message_1: Suppose we have a message "HELLO" and we want to compute its cryptographic hash value using the MD5 hash function. What is the resulting hash value in hexadecimal format?
message_2:
To compute the MD5 hash value of the message "HELLO", you can use an MD5 hash calculator or a programming language with a built-in MD5 hashing function. Here's the resulting hash value in hexadecimal format:

MD5("HELLO") = 8b1a9953c4611296a827abf8c47804d7
